overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking validation against detailed specifications and an SOW.
  The agent first conducted a thorough audit, pinpointing critical missing
  functionalities. Following this, the agent systematically implemented several
  high and medium-priority features. Key additions included a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness, complete with safety warnings, and sophisticated
  detection logic for both Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, integrated into both the web and PDF reports. The
  agent also incorporated a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS) and added a dedicated "Resources & Next Steps" section with
  placeholder outbound links. Finally, the CSV export functionality was
  significantly enhanced to capture all questionnaire data, ensuring
  comprehensive data access. These changes involved updates across types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic.
